args: After enjoying a tasty dinner, Melsa, Elisanne,\nCleo, and Ranzal play a memory-based card game.
The threes are here and here.\nAnd the sevens are here and...\nAh, that one on the edge there.
Hell, ya got it AGAIN! Yer unstoppable\nat this, Melsa.
The only way you could have done that\nwas to memorize all the cards after seeing\nthem onceâ€”which seems impossible.
Well, that explains how you keep winning,\nalthough not the talent itself.
I'm a little jealous, to be honest.
If I had your memory, I'd never have to\nmake a list when I go shopping.
Huh? What? Don't worry about it.\n...Now go for it, Melsa!
You were talking about shopping,\nand... Well, I...
I was thinking that if I went with you,\nyou wouldn't need to make a list.
That would be a tremendous help.
I've been stressing out a little about the\ngrowing number of things I have to buy,\nso by all means come if you are willing.
And thank you as well, Ranzal!
Bwa ha ha! Ain't no need to thank me.\nI'm just glad it worked out for ya.
Wait, why is Melsa thanking YOU, Ranzal?
Now that I think about it, I remember he\nwas giving her some advice earlier.\nThis is all most suspicious.
He was merely trying to help me.
I don't follow. What exactly was he\nhelping you with?
I wished to be better friends with you all,\nbut was unsure how to go about it.
Then Ranzal told me he knew a good\nway to break the iceâ€”a card game.
Yeah, I figured she'd be able to get tight\nwith the group if we all got nice and\nchatty over a deck.
...Perhaps I was wrong about you, Ranzal.
Apparently even HE can do something\ngood every now and then.
Hey, gimme a break! I'm just tryin' to look\nout for the new kid, yeah?
Although I didn't expect her to win every\ndamn hand!

You have nothing to apologize for.
If you do not give your all in every
competition, there is no reason to
even take part.
And on that note, I'm done holdin' back!
C'mon, let's get round two goin'. Oh,\nand this time, I'm playin' for keeps!
You can play for as many keeps as you\nwishâ€”she's still going to win.
Won't know till we go, yeah?\nNow let's DO THIS THING!
The eights're here...and here.\nAnd the nines're here and here!
What a fine memory you have, Ranzal!
Wait, RANZAL's memory is this good?\nWhat's going on here?
If I didn't know better, I'd say he was\nusing a marked deck.

...Not intentionally, anyway. But this deck
is pretty beat up, so ya can tell what card
is what by the scratches and folds on the
back of 'em.
And HOW is that any different from\nintentional cheating?!
It's STRATEGY! Rule number one of any\ncompetition: Make use of whatcha got.
In that case, I, too, shall ï¼‚make use of\nwhat I got.ï¼‚
You should feel lucky I held back.
Held back? Ya just scratched the cards all\nto hell!
Yes, and that magic could have easily\ndestroyed the deck. So be glad that I\nshowed a modicum of restraint.
Come, Melsa. We'll work together to\ndefeat this coward.
That's right. We've been around here\nlonger, so it's our duty to help you win.
Fine then! I'll beat ya with my WITS!\nThis one here...and THIS one!\nAh, crap! That ain't it!
The two is here...and the five is here.\nI believe that makes me the winner.
And now it's time for your lecture, Ranzal.\nDon't cheat when you play games!
A lecture is not necessary, actually.\nI don't mind what he did.
My only goal with the game was to get to\nknow everyone, and I was able to do that.
I feel like I have more friends now,\nwhich makes me very happy.
Heh. Then my plan worked! I pretended to\nbe a heel, and you guys became friends!
I don't think there was any pretending\ninvolved, Ranzal.
This worked out in SPITE of your actions.
Hey, don't be sweatin' the minor details!\nThe end justifies the means and all that.\nAin't that right, Melsa?
Indeed. Thank you all for a wonderful time.
Especially you, Ranzal. You both helped\nme and looked out for me.
Bwa ha ha! Think nothin' of it, kid.
Hey! I just thought of somethin'.\nWould ya do me a favor, Melsa?
I wanna play cards againâ€”but this time,\nI've got an even better game in mind...
There's a better game than this one?
Oh, yeah. It's a blast. It's a card game for\nadults filled with thrills and tensionâ€”and\nwe play for real stakes!
Aaaand that's enough of that. If you'd be so\nkind as to lecture this miscreant, Elisanne?
Ranzal! It is simply inexcusable for you to\nattempt to drag Melsa down to your level,\nwhere only the dregs of humanity exist!
I was JOKIN'! Sheesh! Gimme a break.
*sigh* Melsa, you mustn't grow up to\nbecome like this one.
What? Um, I don't know what you mean.\n...Er, everyone? Please wait for me!
What is this fun new card game?!\nI have to know!
